          <div class="content-container">
            <h3>Usage</h3>
            <p>Used to call out the key product benefits.</p>

            <h4>Layout modes</h4>
            <p>There are two layout modes: desktop, tablet and mobile. Larger screens display the content in a content column. Smaller screens display the content in a vertically stacking content area. </p>
            <hr />
            <h3>CSS</h3>
            <h4>Media queries</h4>
            <p>We are using three breakpoints to handle the changes between desktop, tablet and mobile. Common styles are loaded for the component and then device specific styles are loaded in for each breakpoint into the appropriate stylesheet.</p>
            <h4>SASS Partials</h4>
            <p>You can find the CSS for this component in the following SASS Partials:</p>
            <p>/common-components/product-spotlight.scss</p>
            <p>/large-components/product-spotlight.scss</p>
            <p>/tablet-components/product-spotlight.scss</p>
            <p>/small-components/product-spotlight.scss</p>
            <hr />
            <h3>Component variants</h3>
            <p>We have provided a free text container as a component variant to aid in content migration. Ideally we would like the salient content to be summarised into bulleted points  but for products where this is not available the content can be entered as free text. </p>
            <hr />
            <h3>Responsive Images</h3>
            <p>The bullet arrows are CSS background images. No retina images are supplied as part of this phase but could be incorporated at a later date. </p>
            <hr />
            <h3>SEO implications</h3>
            <p>The summarised bullet points will be some of the first content encountered in the page. There was also discussion about automating the meta description field by copying text entered in the product overview container. It is therefore essential this component is keyword loaded and reflects an accurate picture of the product content within the rest of the copy available. </p>
            <hr />
            <h3>Character limit recommendations</h3>
            <p>Product spotlight bullets: 66 characters per line</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

